      • save

        public boolean save()
        Saves the template, writing it to disk.
        返回:
        true if the template was successfully saved.

      • save

        public boolean save​(boolean writeToDisk)
        Saves the template, either updating the local version or writing it to disk.
        参数:
        writeToDisk - If true, TemplateManager.writeTemplate(net.minecraft.server.MinecraftServer, net.minecraft.util.ResourceLocation) will be called with the template, and its return value will dictate the return value of this method. If false, the template will be updated but not written to disk.
        返回:
        true if the template was successfully saved.

      • load

        public boolean load()
        Loads the given template, both into this structure block and into the world, aborting if the size of the template does not match the size in this structure block.
        返回:
        true if the template was successfully added to the world.

      • load

        public boolean load​(boolean requireMatchingSize)
        Loads the given template, both into this structure block and into the world.
        参数:
        requireMatchingSize - If true, and the size of the loaded template does not match the size in this structure block, the structure will not be loaded into the world and false will be returned. Regardless of the value of this parameter, the size in the structure block will be updated after calling this method.
        返回:
        true if the template was successfully added to the world.

      • getDisplayName

        @Nullable
public ITextComponent getDisplayName()
        Returns a displayable component representing this thing's name. This method should be implemented slightly differently depending on the interface (for technical reasons the same method is used for both IWorldNameable and ICommandSender), but unlike getName() this method will generally behave sanely.
        INameable.getDisplayName()
        A normal component. Might be a translation component or a text component depending on the context. Usually implemented as:
        return this.hasCustomName() ? new
 TextComponentString(this.getName()) : new TextComponentTranslation(this.getName());
        ICommandSender.getDisplayName() and Entity.getDisplayName()
        For most entities, this returns the result of getName(), with scoreboard formatting and a special hover event.
        For non-entity command senders, this will return the result of getName() in a text component.
